illiam the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705189,"age":23,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705190,"age":54,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705191,"age":79,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Robert Waltheham was born in 1236, in Chilton, Suffolk, England. He had at least 1 daughter with Mrs. Robert Waltheham."},"et":{"1236–":"1236–Surnud","1236–Female":"1236–Surnud","1260–Female":"1260–Surnud","1236–Male":"1236–Surnud","1315":"1315","1259":"1259","1236":"1236","1260":"1260","1317":"1317","1290":"1290","Chilton, Suffolk, England":"Chilton, Suffolk, England","England":"England"},"fi":{"1236–":"1236–Kuollut","1236–Female":"1236–Kuollut","1260–Female":"1260–Kuollut","1236–Male":"1236–Kuollut","1315":"1315","1259":"1259","1236":"1236